<TITLE> No bars on telecasting BNP rally live </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 5 (bdnews24.com) There is no embargo on telecasting BNP chief Khaleda Zia's speech at the BNP rally in Rajshahi, a government handout said on Wednesday. Khaleda arrived in the northwestern district city on Wednesday afternoon to attend the divisional meeting. Several national newspapers reported on Wednesday--and the BNP itself also alleged-- that the government was going to impose a restriction on live telecast of the rally. The handout termed the news 'misleading' and 'ill-motivated'. The government also said that the handout had been circulated to clarify its position. Earlier, different TV channels telecast Khaleda's speech from Chittagong on Mar 29 and Khulna on Apr 18. bd
